narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If it's around and you're a music major looking for a senior seminar, you have to take this.
Yes, I would recommend this class to other students. It is a great opportunity to learn in deeper detail the works of Bach and perform them.

I would summarize the course as a wonderful opportunity to be acquainted with baroque music and historically informed performance practice. We use baroque bows and even have the chance to play on some baroque instruments. It was a great experience for me to play on a baroque violin and feel the difference between that, and my modern instrument. I would most definitely recommend this course to a fellow student. I believe that getting to know Prof. Mealy is a special and rare opportunity that should not be missed for anyone serious about music!
A combination of lectures on the life and chamber music of bach with masterclasses about Bach's chamber music. Ends with a performance.
